"title": "8427: evangelism, kinds of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8427: evangelism, kinds of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture recognises that evangelism takes place in a variety of contexts, and offers models for evangelism in today's church.</p>\n<h2>Public evangelism</h2>\n<h3>Preaching in synagogues</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:1\">ACT 14:1</a></strong> <em>Paul begins his evangelism in Gentile cities by building links within the Jewish community.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:14-Acts13:16\">ACT 13:14–13:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:42-Acts13:44\">ACT 13:42–13:44</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:2\">ACT 17:2</a> <em>in Thessalonica</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:10\">ACT 17:10</a> <em>in Berea</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:17\">ACT 17:17</a> <em>in Athens</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:4\">ACT 18:4</a> <em>in Corinth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:8\">ACT 19:8</a> <em>in Ephesus</em></p>\n<h3>Preaching in recognised meeting-places</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:19-Acts17:23\">ACT 17:19–17:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:25\">ACT 5:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:27-Acts10:28\">ACT 10:27–10:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:13\">ACT 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:9\">ACT 19:9</a></p>\n<h3>Making a public defence to accusers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:37-Acts22:1\">ACT 21:37–22:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:7-Acts4:12\">ACT 4:7–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:1-Acts7:2\">ACT 7:1–7:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:10\">ACT 24:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:1\">ACT 26:1</a></p>\n<h2>Personal evangelism</h2>\n<h3>Giving personal testimony</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:1-1John1:3\">1JN 1:1–1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:19\">MRK 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:39\">JHN 4:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:9-Acts26:18\">ACT 26:9–26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:16\">1CO 7:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1-1Pet3:2\">1PE 3:1–3:2</a></p>\n<h3>Evangelism in homes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:24-Acts10:25\">ACT 10:24–10:25</a></strong> <em>Peter visits Cornelius' home to speak to those assembled.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29\">LUK 5:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:26\">ACT 18:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:30-Acts28:31\">ACT 28:30–28:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:17\">ACT 9:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:12\">ACT 22:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:32-Acts16:34\">ACT 16:32–16:34</a></p>\n<h2>Evangelism in strategic areas</h2>\n<h3>Going to major centres</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:12\">ACT 16:12</a> <em>Philippi</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:1\">ACT 17:1</a> <em>Thessalonica</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:15\">ACT 17:15</a> <em>Athens</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:1\">ACT 18:1</a> <em>Corinth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:19\">ACT 18:19</a> <em>Ephesus</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:11\">ACT 23:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:14\">ACT 28:14</a></p>\n<h3>Going into new territories</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:20\">ROM 15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:23-Rom15:24\">ROM 15:23–15:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:15-2Cor10:16\">2CO 10:15–10:16</a></p>\n<h2>Evangelism among strategic people</h2>\n<h3>Speaking to prominent people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:8\">ACT 18:8</a></strong> <em>Though the gospel is for all people without distinction, evangelism among certain people and groups enabled the message to spead further.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:7\">ACT 13:7</a> <em>Paul before Sergius Paulus, proconsul of Cyprus</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:24\">ACT 24:24</a> <em>Paul before Felix and his wife</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:8-Acts25:9\">ACT 25:8–25:9</a> <em>Paul before Festus</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:11-Acts25:12\">ACT 25:11–25:12</a> <em>Paul appeals to Caesar</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:2-Acts26:3\">ACT 26:2–26:3</a> <em>Paul before King Agrippa</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:7-Acts28:8\">ACT 28:7–28:8</a> <em>Paul in the home of the chief official on Malta</em></p>\n<h3>Evangelising households</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:34\">ACT 16:34</a></strong> <em>The conversion of the head of the household was often accompanied by the conversion of the whole family group.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:53\">JHN 4:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:14\">ACT 11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:8\">ACT 18:8</a></p>\n<h2>Using literature in evangelism</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:30-John20:31\">JHN 20:30–20:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:1-Luke1:4\">LUK 1:1–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:1-Acts1:2\">ACT 1:1–1:2</a></p>\n<h2>Appealing to Scripture in evangelism</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:22-Acts26:23\">ACT 26:22–26:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:35\">ACT 8:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:43\">ACT 10:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:22-Acts13:23\">ACT 13:22–13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:2-Rom1:3\">ROM 1:2–1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:25-Rom16:26\">ROM 16:25–16:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3-1Cor15:4\">1CO 15:3–15:4</a></p>\n<h2>Signs and wonders in evangelism</h2>\n<h3>Miracles confirm the message</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:6\">ACT 8:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:17-Mark16:20\">MRK 16:17–16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:14\">ACT 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:10-Acts19:12\">ACT 19:10–19:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:4-1Cor2:5\">1CO 2:4–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:3-Heb2:4\">HEB 2:3–2:4</a></p>\n<h3>Miracles give opportunity for preaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:9-Acts3:16\">ACT 3:9–3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:5-Acts2:14\">ACT 2:5–2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:8-Acts14:11\">ACT 14:8–14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:26-Acts16:31\">ACT 16:26–16:31</a></p>\n<h3>Miracles result in people believing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:40-Acts9:42\">ACT 9:40–9:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:31\">JHN 7:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:45\">JHN 11:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:33-Acts9:35\">ACT 9:33–9:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:10-Acts13:12\">ACT 13:10–13:12</a></p>\n<h2>The response to evangelism</h2>\n<h3>Acceptance of the message</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:37-Acts2:41\">ACT 2:37–2:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:4\">ACT 4:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:4\">ACT 17:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:34\">ACT 17:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:17-Acts19:20\">ACT 19:17–19:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:13\">1TH 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Rejection of the message</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:2\">HEB 4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:16\">ROM 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:50-Acts13:51\">ACT 13:50–13:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:32\">ACT 17:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:6\">ACT 18:6</a></p>",
